    "source_commit": "8fec14c",
    "notes": [
      "JS lifecycle oracle proof for source Game.onStop() ending a 4P match when exactly one present avatar is at max score.",
      "The harness starts a real all-present 4P source round with max_score 3, waits for delayed PrintManager.start timers, keeps avatar 1 on a slow safe path, then forces avatars 4, 3, and 2 into separate wall-death source updates.",
      "The separate forced deaths give avatars 4, 3, and 2 round scores 0, 1, and 2; avatar 1 receives the 4P survivor bonus and becomes the unique leader at score 3, so source isWon() emits end instead of a next round.",
      "This is a JS-oracle and Python source-runner fixture only. It does not claim public-env parity, vector lifecycle parity, replay, trainer observations, bonuses, wire behavior, or pixels."
    ]
  },
